name: "Animal (I Think)" by Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
description: [Ink on reclaimed paper with digital embellishments and color.] Automatic drawing created in a trance and then enhanced with high-tech digital software. Well, by "trance" I mean I was really tired, and by "high-tech" blah blah, yeah, I mean my phone. Doesn't diminish the obvious HORROR that this creature clearly invokes. (Does it?) ---Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
